    "body": "## Summary\n\n- add the canonical Verdikta backlog and issue workflow guide\n- add a root `AGENTS.md` with mandatory agent-facing rules\n- link the workflow from the README and contributor guide\n- expose the guide in the MkDocs Contributing navigation\n\n## Why\n\nVerdikta now uses one cross-repository Master Backlog. Humans and automated agents need a stable source for repository ownership, initiative structure, Project views and fields, Ready criteria, intake, execution transitions, blockers, PR closure, and bulk-change safety.\n\n## Validation\n\n- `git diff --check`\n- verified every local README/AGENTS/contributor link resolves to a tracked file\n- verified the guide contains the approved Status, Readiness, Priority, Size, Area, view, issue-template, and execution rules\n- MkDocs build not run because MkDocs is not installed in the available environment",
