    "body": "## Goal\n\nObtain and operationalize legal guidance that clearly defines how Verdikta can describe and support criteria-based settlement without implying that it replaces courts, lawyers, or regulated arbitration.\n\n## Context\n\nParent initiative: https://github.com/verdikta/verdikta-roadmap/issues/4\n\nThis is distinct from the custody and operating-posture legal gate in https://github.com/verdikta/verdikta-agents/issues/112. That issue concerns the Agents soft launch; this work concerns protocol language and use cases across bounties, prediction markets, DAO grants, escrow releases, and integrations.\n\nExternal counsel input and a responsible internal decision owner are required before this issue can be marked Ready for final sign-off.\n\n## Acceptance criteria\n\n- [ ] Counsel or qualified reviewers answer when product “resolution” language could be treated as regulated arbitration or another regulated activity.\n- [ ] The guidance identifies public terms to prefer and avoid, including treatment of “dispute,” “arbitration,” “court,” “jury,” and “no human in the loop.”\n- [ ] Supported use cases, high-risk or prohibited use cases, and cases requiring additional human/admin review are documented.\n- [ ] Required disclaimers, consents, terms, privacy considerations, and integration responsibilities are identified.\n- [ ] The distinction between a protocol settlement signal and an application's legal or operational decision is explicit.\n- [ ] A concise internal language guide and implementation checklist are produced.\n- [ ] Follow-up site, terms, documentation, and integration changes are linked without publishing confidential legal advice.\n\n## Validation\n\nAttach or reference the approved decision record, language guide, risk matrix, and resulting implementation issues. Review representative bounty, agent-commerce, prediction-market, DAO-grant, and escrow copy against the guidance.\n\n## Scope\n\nIn scope:\n\n- Protocol and application positioning\n- Use-case guardrails\n- Disclaimers, consents, and review requirements\n- Internal guidance derived from legal advice\n\nOut of scope:\n\n- Public disclosure of privileged advice\n- The separate Agents custody/launch legal gate\n- Representing Verdikta as legal counsel or a court",
