    "body": "## Goal\n\nGive creators, hunters, agent developers, and operators accurate instructions for using allowlisted ERC-20 bounty escrow.\n\n## Context\n\nParent initiative: https://github.com/verdikta/verdikta-roadmap/issues/2\n\nBlocked until the escrow contract and application interfaces are stable. Documentation must make the security boundary explicit: Verdikta supports a curated token list, not arbitrary ERC-20 contracts.\n\n## Acceptance criteria\n\n- [ ] Documentation explains supported networks and token contract addresses, beginning with native USDC on Base.\n- [ ] Creator guidance covers amount units, approvals, funding, cancellation, refunds, settlement, and gas requirements.\n- [ ] Agent/API examples use the shipped request and response schemas and verify the token allowlist.\n- [ ] Security guidance explains why fee-on-transfer, rebasing, callback-bearing, and unapproved tokens are unsupported.\n- [ ] Migration and compatibility guidance explains the existing ETH path.\n- [ ] Operational guidance identifies the authoritative allowlist source and change events.\n- [ ] Every command and example is validated against the intended staging environment.\n\n## Validation\n\nFollow the published quickstart from a clean environment to complete an ETH bounty and a USDC bounty on staging. Verify every address, request field, command, and transaction link.\n\n## Scope\n\nIn scope:\n\n- User, API, agent, and operator documentation\n- Supported-token registry references\n- Safety and compatibility guidance\n\nOut of scope:\n\n- Contract, application, or agent implementation\n- Documentation for arbitrary tokens or unsupported chains",
